    • getWeatherData

      public List<WeatherData> getWeatherData(String url)
      Fetches weather data from FMI API from the given URL. Forms WeatherData objects from the fetched data.
      Parameters:
      url - The URL to fetch data from
      Returns:
      List of WeatherData objects

    • getDailyWeatherData

      public List<WeatherData> getDailyWeatherData(LocalDateTime start, LocalDateTime end, BoundingCoordinates coords)
      Fetches daily weather data from FMI API from given time period and coordinates
      Parameters:
      start - Start time of the time period to fetch data from
      end - End time of the time period to fetch data from
      coords - Bounding coordinates for the area to fetch data from
      Returns:
      List of WeatherData objects. One object for each day in the time period.

    • getHourlyForecastWeatherData

      public List<WeatherData> getHourlyForecastWeatherData(LocalDateTime start, LocalDateTime end, BoundingCoordinates coords)
      Fetches hourly weather data from FMI API from given time period and coordinates.
      Parameters:
      start - Start time of the time period to fetch data from
      end - End time of the time period to fetch data from
      coords - Bounding coordinates for the area to fetch data from
      Returns:
      List of WeatherData objects. One object for each hour in the time period.

    • calculateAverages

      private List<WeatherData> calculateAverages(List<WeatherData> weathers, boolean daily)
      Calculates average weathers from the given WeatherData objects
      Parameters:
      weathers - List of WeatherData objects to calculate averages from
      daily - If true forms one WeatherData object for each day in the time period. If false forms one WeatherData object for each hour in the time period.
      Returns:
      List of average WeatherData objects

    • getPastCloudAndWindData

      private ArrayList<WeatherData> getPastCloudAndWindData(LocalDateTime start, LocalDateTime end, String coordsString)
      Fetches observed cloudiness and wind speed from FMI API from the given time period and coordinates
      Parameters:
      start - Start time of the time period to fetch data from
      end - End time of the time period to fetch data from
      coordsString - Coordinate area as a string in the form MinLon,MinLat,MaxLon,MaxLat
      Returns:
      List of WeatherData objects

    • getForecasts

      private List<WeatherData> getForecasts(LocalDateTime start, LocalDateTime end, String coordsString, int timeStep)
      Fetches forecasts for temperature and wind speed from FMI API from the given time period and coordinates
      Parameters:
      start - Start time of the time period to fetch data from
      end - End time of the time period to fetch data from
      coordsString - Coordinate area as a string in the form Latitude,Longitude
      timeStep - The time interval at which data is fetched in minutes
      Returns:
      List of WeatherData objects
